by 6 sample\ncolumns named sample_0..sample_5. The first 3 samples are condition_A and the last\n3 are condition_B. Rows starting with `ERCC-` must be dropped.\n\nRun DESeq2 differential expression (`design = ~condition`) and produce two outputs:\n  - `output/deseq2_up.txt`: genes with log2FoldChange >= 2 (rownames = Geneid)\n  - `output/deseq2_down.txt`: genes with log2FoldChange <= -2\nBoth must be written with `write.table(..., col.names=TRUE, row.names=TRUE, quote=FALSE)`.\nFilter out rows where log2FoldChange or padj is NA before the up/down split.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/deseq2_up.txt` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: deseq2_up.txt, deseq2_down.txt under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"featureCounts_output.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"featureCounts_output.txt\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/deseq2_up.txt` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_R2Gk2PHSBEiBQcua7VlujgWL", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the necessary R library (DESeq2) for differential expression analysis.\\n2. Read the input count matrix from `input/featureCounts_output.txt`.\\n3. Remove rows starting with `ERCC-` from the count matrix.\\n4. Prepare the DESeq2 dataset using the count data and condition information.\\n5. Run the DESeq2 analysis to obtain differential expression results.\\n6. Filter the results to remove rows with NA values in `log2FoldChange` or `padj`.\\n7. Identify upregulated genes with `log2FoldChange >= 2` and write to `output/deseq2_up.txt`.\\n8. Identify downregulated genes with `log2FoldChange <= -2` and write to `output/deseq2_down.txt`.\\n9. Ensure the output files are written with the correct parameters: `col.names=TRUE`, `row.names=TRUE`, `quote=FALSE`.\\n10. Verify the existence of `output/deseq2_up.txt` and call `submit_done(success=true)` if present.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (851 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_R2Gk2PHSBEiBQcua7VlujgWL"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_2xOgIVQCddXqovGp3Q8Fyvbv", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/featureCounts_output.txt\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}, {"id": "call_EPA45s2xTPfG9m5ct8cUnOrQ", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(DESeq2)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}, {"id": "call_w15DqjMY7Yk18rJ9SxBF5nYe", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "list_workdir"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Geneid\tChr\tStart\tEnd\tStrand\tLength\tsample_0\tsample_1\tsample_2\tsample_3\tsample_4\tsample_5\nGENE_0000\tchr1\t1000\t1500\t+\t500\t1200\t1457\t1254\t7553\t7352\t10821\nGENE_0001\tchr1\t1001\t1501\t+\t500\t1021\t1138\t1001\t1067\t1167\t1000\nGENE_0002\tchr1\t1002\t1502\t+\t500\t486\t484\t445\t450\t426\t507\nGENE_0003\tchr1\t1003\t1503\t+\t500\t1751\t1699\t1527\t1438\t1824\t1525\nGENE_0004\tchr1\t1004\t1504\t+\t500\t230\t228\t227\t222\t206\t236\nGENE_0005\tchr1\t1005\t1505\t+\t500\t348\t293\t309\t335\t315\t338\nGENE_0006\tchr1\t1006\t1506\t+\t500\t1118\t1072\t1291\t1332\t1411\t1363\nGENE_0007\tchr1\t1007\t1507\t+\t500\t1605\t1702\t1898\t1750\t1752\t1665\nGENE_0008\tchr1\t1008\t1508\t+\t500\t632\t628\t519\t620\t602\t550\nGENE_0009\tchr1\t1009\t1509\t+\t500\t959\t1142\t1037\t1013\t1051\t1098\nGENE_0010\tchr1\t1010\t1510\t+\t500\t1420\t1797\t1788\t1590\t1425\t1842\nGENE_0011\tchr1\t1011\t1511\t+\t500\t1347\t1143\t1267\t1173\t1361\t1196\nGENE_0012\tchr1\t1012\